<html>

<head>
    <h2>JavaScript Error Handling and arrow function</h2>

    <p>This example demonstrates how to use <b>catch</b> to display an error.</p>

    <p id="result"></p>
    <script>
        let x = 10;
        let y = 0;

        try {
            let z = x / y; // This will cause an error (division by zero)
            document.getElementById("result").innerHTML = "Result: " + z;
        } catch (error) {
            document.getElementById("result").innerHTML = "Error: " + error.message;
        }
